snippet.textDisplay: Enough of this "Pakistan has a talent in music'  bullsh*t. snippet.textDisplay: Honestly a masterpiece. Not too many songs leave an impact when listened for the first time. I have just listened it and I am in love with the melody. Heads off to Shuja Haider for this beautiful composition. Attaullah EsaKhelvi is one of the legendary singers in sub-continent and his rustic voice is undoubtedly catchy. The younger Esakhelvi did his best to match his father's skills. A 10/10 from my side.
